17 March 2016On 21 March 2016, the Deputy Minister of Communications, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams in collaboration with the National Application Centre and Department of Correctional Services, will embark on an oversight visit to the Boksburg Juvenile Correctional Centre.The purpose of the visit is to assess the Information and Communication Technology (ICT) sponsorship which was made to the Correctional Centre at the launch of the Education for Offenders &amp; Reading Redemption Programme in 2014. Additionally, the Deputy Minister will engage with the community, Centre personnel and inmates on Human Rights Day to honour this historic day and celebrate how far the nation has progressed in this regard.Members of the media are cordially invited to the outreach programme and the details are as follows: Date: Monday, 21 March 2016 Time: 11H00 14H30 Venue: Boksburg Juvenile Correctional Centre, Barry Maria Rod, Boksburg East, BoksburgPlease note that opportunity will be given to journalists for interviews and photo opportunities. For more information &amp; RSVP please contact Jacob Molete on 073 657 5680 or jacobm@gcis.gov.zaEnquiries: Peter Gumede: 083 570 8080 or Nthabeleng Mokitimi: 073 222 5522Issued by GCIS on behalf of The Ministry of Communications